<br>
I think the whole &quot;dirty secret&quot; Brutin alludes to is that Saga has people in it.  Some of the people are RP 98% of the time, some of them RP 75% of the time, some even RP only 50% of the time and make concessions for game mechanics and might even try to build those mechanics into things consitant with how our characters might view the world, though that can be a a difficult thing as well.  I dunno, there might even be some of the people in Saga that RP 15% of the time, such as only when they are in /say and others are Rping to them.  <br>
<br>
Ditry secrets.. so incredibly vile.  <br>
<br>
Saga's people have even been known to talk in guild chat or channel chat (marked as ooc) about someone petitioning to get out from under the world or even trying to figure out ways to rescue the player from the mechanics gone bad and being stuck in a place for over 2 hours without even a shred of a comment from a guide let alone a GM.  Saga's people have been known to care about the people behind the characters.  Saga's people have been known have OOC conversations in the OOC part of their message board.  Saga's people have been known to see humor in a situation and not take -everything- so excpetionally incredibly serious.  Saga's people have been known to even joke around with each other in guild chat and their channel chat.  Saga's people have been known to support each other and encourage each other in RP and OOC situations.  <br>
<br>
Saga as a guild does not claim to be the server's authority on RP or even that it is a 110% of the time, no slacking, RP only guild.  Saga as a guild -does- foster and encourage RP both online and off.  Saga's people do particitpate in -some- of each other's stories but there is never a requirement for all members of the guild to be included in a storyline or that any storyline be opened up to include every member whether the writer wishes it or not and whether the other members wish it or not.<br>
<br>
What business does this have being on a public board?  None.  The only reason some of us are posting is defensively because it is very very hard listening to a bully shout and posture telling you how horrid you are and saying you must agree with him if you don't say anything.  To say something perpetuates the mud and filth.  Not to say anything... well.. the bully perpetuates is by running around saying &quot;I'm right, I'm right, neener neener.&quot;<br>
<br>
As I have said before in other places and maybe I need to say it more here... I am me, no more, no less, just me.  I do not seek to be more, I do not seek to be anything which I am not.  I am jsut and only me.  I am the world's greatest authority on nothing but me.  I am a member of an outstanding RP highly encouraged guild on the Firiona Vie server which is a RP preferred server of the Everquest game.  But I am still only me.  I have never said I am the world's greatest RPer or that my RP matches anyone else's RP, just that I RP Caillou the way -I- see Caillou (or she sees herself when she does a bit of taking over).  I don't stay IC 200% of the time on line and off whenever Caillou's name is mentioned.  I do converse in  OOC via tells and even group (when there is a limited number of us and it is not a pages long conversation when I can and have asked to take it to email or some other our of game medium) and have even made an occassional OOC comment on guildchat and channel chat, especially when appropriate (i.e. &quot;((are the boats broken?))&quot;).<br>
<br>
I am tired of Brutin.  I am tired of -anyone- being holier than thou and insisting only their method of RP is the proper method.<br>
<br>
I hope that now that the &quot;secret&quot; is out, this can go the way of the Dodo.<br>
