<br>
Now, to the dirty part.  No specifics here mind you.<br>
<br>
I was inside Saga, and I know that what you tell people on the outside is a lie.  Lying is a lower moral character trait.  If you want to lie to yourself, so be it, but don't lie to others, if you are a Lemon and want to be an Orange, get over it (this alludes to a different post but speaks for itself on it's face). <br>
<br>
What Saga comes out here and says is the untruth, and it is said in such a way as to make themselves look better at a time of crisis, namely, when the shit talkers are out in force. <br>
<br>
This provides a brow beating to someone and then reinforced by a guild against them.  If someone in Saga has a problem with someone, go alone and fight it out.  But if you step up as as a guild then be prepared to be treated as such. <br>
<br>
Case in point, this little calling me out thing Siffo did.  <br>
<br>
It blew up in his face because believe it or not, I was nonconfrontational.  For me to show up here sticking my finger in his face must have been a real shock.  But Kul and you and Bridh and Quea just had to come over and help, you had to dig, hell you did poorCaillou at the very first appearance here, didn't you?  Did you not set that tone yourself?  And why were you here? Are you Siffo's lover? Sister? Mother?  Nope, You are Saga.  <br>
<br>
You were all here because you were Saga, and after you got pummelled and you realized I wasn't going away, there comes Valquiss, the old wizzened member who stepped it and Mixxied [sic] it up with Sarhea but tried to put the &quot;we are Saga&quot; information in, much as Fayd had done in the one that started this.  And then he proceeded to play the same games as you guys.  So despite my getting along with him I had to spank dat ass too.  Cuz that is what I said I would do.<br>
<br>
Notice of course that the good shit is ignored because of your attitude.  Katryna comes along and amist the thickest of the arguing and name calling she only wishes me good things.  Anyone remember that?  And Rorac who I think I know but he dropped his &quot;k&quot; somewhere felt compelled to defend himself.  That in itself is a shame and I apologize to them both, but my point is, if you had the energy to defend your guild from the outside, why couldn't you defend it on the inside?<br>
<br>
So that in a nutshell brings us up to just about what that was all about, Siffo and I have both been asked by different parties and I believe some of the same to let this matter lie.  And we both agreed.  And down the drain it was going.  <br>
<br>
Until you. <br>
<br>
Yeah, other people are posting, but they aren't Saga.  So that means I have to step in and possibly risk reigniting this thing.  <br>
<br>
Now, I have explained myself.<br>
<br>
Let Saga do what it wants to itself, if it chooses not to police itself, then so be it, that is there choice.  I am okay with that, but if you show publically and yap away something you are not, then I have to stop you, that is lying.  And you use that lying to hurt people other than me.  <br>
<br>
I love Saga still.  I have serious issues with some of the people you consider worthy of calling Saga.  But then, that is because I DID help form Saga, I was one of the main yappers back then that set it up.  I think I should know how it goes.  <br>
<br>
And as Valquiss said, guilds change.  I can agree with that, but realize, that what you change into doesn't give you the right to use your old reputation, if you turn OOC, then that is fine, no one argues that, but if you come out and pretend to be IC after that, there is a problem.  <br>
<br>
Everyone knows Saga from having been IC.  Now that you are turning OOC it is unfair to attack people on any board in any forum and then claim a right to the higher reputation IC priviledges give you.  That is chicken shit.  <br>
<br>
And that is why I am here.  <br>
<br>
If I find another guild doing it, I will lambaste them as well.  It's something that I think everyone can agree on that a RP server just doesn't need.  IC is the name of the game, and from what I can see of the Pofolk here in these threads, ain't but 3 out of 8 of you in Saga doing it.<br>
<br>
You may go now.<br>
<br>
